Quebecor Inc &lt;PQB.A>, the Canadianpublishing concern, is issuing a 60 mln dlr convertible bonddue May 14, 1997 bearing an indicated coupon of 5-3/4 to sixpct, said Merrill Lynch Capital Markets as lead manager.    The issue will be priced to have a conversion premium of 22to 25 pct, with final terms to be set on Monday, April 6. Thecompany's stock last traded on the Toronto Stock Exchange at19-3/8. The securities will be listed in Luxembourg and areavailable in denominations of 1,000 and 10,000 dlrs.    Fees include a one pct combined management and underwritingand a one pct selling concession. REUTER&#3;